+# AI PM Case Studies
+
+A portfolio of public PM case studies on AI products — written as if I were responsible for the next 18 months of revenue growth on each one. Built to demonstrate AI-native PM craft: strategy + measurement + shipping, not just opinions.
+
+## What each case study contains
+
+Every case study follows the same 7-section spine — the structure of a real PM strategy doc, not a blog post:
+
+1. **Market analysis** — TAM/SAM, competitive segments, where the market is going
+2. **SWOT** — grounded in public evidence, cross-linked to opportunities
+3. **Revenue-growth opportunities** — ICE-scored, with TAM math, ranked, recommended pair
+4. **Prototype** — interactive HTML mockup validating the top opportunity
+5. **Evaluation framework** — north-star metric, 3-layer evals (capability / calibration / product), A/B design
+6. **Risks & kill criteria** — top-N risks with numeric trigger signals and mitigation options
+7. **Launch & growth plan** — 90-day timeline, distribution, pricing, growth loops, what NOT to do
+
+Plus a **self-contained `walkthrough.html`** per case study — the showcase artifact for interviews.
+
+## Case studies
+
+| Product | Status | Thesis | Walkthrough |
+|---|---|---|---|
+| [**Claude Code**](./claude-code/) | ✅ Complete | 5–10× revenue in 18 months by anchoring on Enterprise + GitHub-native distribution before chasing Web/Async | [HTML](./claude-code/walkthrough.html) |
+| Cursor | 🔜 Planned | TBD | — |
+| Granola | 🔜 Planned | TBD | — |
+| Perplexity | 🔜 Planned | TBD | — |
+| NotebookLM | 🔜 Planned | TBD | — |
+| Replit Agent | 🔜 Planned | TBD | — |
+
+## How these are built
+
+Each case study is produced via parallel multi-agent orchestration in Claude Code — one agent per section, then a synthesis agent for the walkthrough HTML. The methodology is itself part of the interview signal: leveraging AI to compress what would historically be a 2-week deep dive into an afternoon, while raising the floor on rigor (every section gets dedicated focus).
+
+## Why these case studies
+
+Most AI-PM portfolios show **toolkits and demos**. Few show **strategic thinking applied to real products at real scale**. These case studies are the bridge — they show I can:
+
+- Frame a product's market position and where it's heading
+- Find the opportunities that matter and rank them with discipline (ICE + TAM math, not vibes)
+- Build a prototype to validate the top opportunity, not just write about it
+- Design the evals that would tell us we're winning before the leading indicators flip
+- Identify what kills the launch and what would make me walk away
+- Sequence a launch with named distribution channels and growth loops
+
+## Author
+
+Tracy Chen — chenxi.tracy@gmail.com
