+<!-- ============================== SECTION 5: EVAL ============================== -->
+<section id="eval">
+  <div class="wrap">
+    <div class="section-head fade-up">
+      <span class="eyebrow">05 · How I'd measure success</span>
+      <h2>One north star, three eval layers, four pitfalls.</h2>
+      <p class="lede">Capability says the model <em>can</em>. Calibration says the model <em>knows what it can</em>. Product says the user <em>gets value</em>. Conflating these is the #1 reason AI products ship broken.</p>
+    </div>
+
+    <div class="nsm fade-up">
+      <div class="label">North-star metric</div>
+      <div class="metric">Weekly Active Coders with ≥1 completed task <span style="color:var(--accent)">(WAC-1)</span></div>
+      <p class="why">A "completed task" = a user-initiated session that ends in either (a) accepted code shipped to a branch/PR, or (b) explicit thumbs-up + session-end. Not a turn. Not a message. <strong>A unit of work the user kept.</strong></p>
+    </div>
+
+    <div class="tree fade-up" aria-label="Metric tree">
+<div class="row l0">[L0] NORTH STAR · WAC-1</div>
+<div class="row l1"><span class="pipe">├──</span> [L1] Activation rate — % new signups to first completed task in 7d</div>
+<div class="row l2"><span class="pipe">│    ├──</span> Time-to-first-task (median min, signup → first accepted)</div>
+<div class="row l2"><span class="pipe">│    ├──</span> First-session task-success %</div>
+<div class="row l2"><span class="pipe">│    └──</span> First-week NPS (post-activation survey)</div>
+<div class="row l1"><span class="pipe">├──</span> [L1] Task throughput — completed tasks / WAC / week</div>
+<div class="row l2"><span class="pipe">│    ├──</span> Median turns-per-completed-task (floor ~2)</div>
+<div class="row l2"><span class="pipe">│    └──</span> Tool-call success rate (Edit/Bash/Read no-error %)</div>
+<div class="row l1"><span class="pipe">├──</span> [L1] Quality / trust — does the work survive contact w/ reality</div>
+<div class="row l2"><span class="pipe">│    ├──</span> Suggestion acceptance rate (accepted / shown)</div>
+<div class="row l2"><span class="pipe">│    ├──</span> Post-accept revert rate within 24h</div>
+<div class="row l2"><span class="pipe">│    └──</span> Hallucination rate on codebase claims</div>
+<div class="row l1"><span class="pipe">└──</span> [L1] Retention — WAC-1 cohort retention at W4 / W12</div>
+<div class="row l2"><span class="pipe">     ├──</span> Repeat task rate (% users w/ ≥3 completed tasks/wk)</div>
+<div class="row l2"><span class="pipe">     └──</span> Multi-repo usage (% users on ≥2 repos in 4 wks)</div>
+    </div>
+
+    <div class="eval-layers fade-up">
+      <div class="layer l1">
+        <span class="num">Layer 1</span>
+        <h4>Capability</h4>
+        <p class="sub">Does the agent get the task right?</p>
+        <ul>
+          <li>250 real coding tasks + 50 curated edge cases, refreshed quarterly, held private</li>
+          <li>Nightly on prod + every candidate checkpoint</li>
+          <li><strong>Gate:</strong> promotion blocked if pass-rate regresses &gt;2pp</li>
+        </ul>
+      </div>
+      <div class="layer l2">
+        <span class="num">Layer 2</span>
+        <h4>Calibration</h4>
+        <p class="sub">Does the agent know when it's wrong?</p>
+        <ul>
+          <li>When the model says "this works," is it true? Target ≥85% precision</li>
+          <li>Hallucination rate on codebase facts: &lt;3%</li>
+          <li>Surrender quality: useful clarifying question vs. fabricate? Rubric 0–3</li>
+        </ul>
+      </div>
+      <div class="layer l3">
+        <span class="num">Layer 3</span>
+        <h4>Product</h4>
+        <p class="sub">Does the developer actually succeed?</p>
+        <ul>
+          <li>End-to-end task success from real telemetry</li>
+          <li>Time-to-first-merge as headline activation metric</li>
+          <li>Trust score: 60% behavioral + 40% survey</li>
+          <li>Cost-to-value: $ per completed task by type</li>
+        </ul>
+      </div>
+    </div>
+
+    <div class="callout red fade-up">
+      <h4>Eval pitfalls to avoid</h4>
+      <ul style="margin:8px 0 0;padding-left:20px;color:var(--ink-2);font-size:.94rem;line-height:1.6">
+        <li><strong>Benchmark hacking.</strong> SWE-bench stopped predicting real-world success once labs trained on adjacent data. Keep a private hold-out, never publish, refresh quarterly.</li>
+        <li><strong>Survivorship bias on completed sessions.</strong> Acceptance rate looks great if you only measure users who came back. Always bucket session-abandons; rage-quit rate is a guardrail.</li>
+        <li><strong>Cost-blind eval.</strong> A 5pp quality boost at 4× cost is a P&amp;L disaster dressed as a win. Every capability eval reports cost in the same row.</li>
+      </ul>
+    </div>
+  </div>
+</section>
